{"key":"post-9290772","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9290772</id>\n<content>I would recommend any mushroom grower to purchase an extra cool mist humidifier and run it 24/7 in your house all winter.&amp;nbsp; Try to get your indoor humidity to 40% to 50% and not only will you feel and breathe better, your energy bills will be much lower, since humid air holds the heat better than dry air.(thermal mass)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With a given amount of moisture in the air, if you raise the temperature by 20F, the RH is roughly cut in half.&amp;nbsp;  Therefore, if your outdoor dewpoints are in the single digits and you heat the house to 70F, your indoor humidity is extremely low, around 10% or even less.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9290846</next>\n<prev>9290522</prev>\n<first>9289339</first>\n<last>9290901</last>\n<when>1227372969</when>\n<utime>11/22/08 06:56 PM</utime>\n</post>"}